Acceptance: Authorized users can request reviewers under the ordinary metadata policy after displaying the PR and selected reviewers. PR review submission (comment, approve, or request changes) is a separate high-risk App-attributed action: display the PR, exact head SHA, review kind, and governing policy; revalidate the head, self-review rule, duplicate state, permission, and policy immediately before submission. In P19 it is available only inside the named, time-bounded pilot behind an explicit gate that is off by default; outside that pilot it is denied and must not be presented as production-ready. Production availability waits for P21 to migrate the action to audited User_required attribution and pass its enablement gate. If P21 user authorization is disabled, incomplete, revoked, or unavailable, deny the action without App or PAT fallback. GitHub rejection and projection/reconciliation failures produce actionable, projection-safe receipts. Canonical contract: docs/plans/2026-07-12-github-item-room-routing.md.